      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "WHEN WE BEHOLD Your heavens, the work of Your fingers,\nthe moon and stars that You set in place\nWhat are we humans that You are mindful of us?\nWe mortals that You take note of us?\nYou made us little less than divine,\nadorned us with glory and majesty.\nYou gave us dominion over Your handiwork,\nlaying the world at our feet...\nhow majestic is Your name throughout the earth!\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ, הַטוֹב שִׁמְךְ וּלְךָ נָאֶה לְהוֹדוֹת.\nBaruch atah, Adonai, hatov shimcha ul'cha na-eh l'hodot.",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
